%C A009991 Same as Pisot sequences E(1, 47), L(1, 47), P(1, 47), T(1, 47). Essentially same as Pisot sequences E(47, 2209), L(47, 2209), P(47, 2209), T(47, 2209). See A008776 for definitions of Pisot sequences.
%C A009991 The compositions of n in which each natural number is colored by one of p different colors are called p-colored compositions of n. For n >= 1, a(n) equals the number of 47-colored compositions of n such that no adjacent parts have the same color. - _Milan Janjic_, Nov 17 2011
